Any Bungoma official found to have been involved in corruption or nepotism will be sacked, Governor
Wyclife Wangamati has said. Speaking at St
Patrick's Pastoral Centre in Kabula on Monday, Wangamati told his cabinet to serve residents with integrity. "I demand maximum integrity from you. I will not entertain any form of corruption because my promise to the people was to faithfully serve them," Wangamati said when he opened a week-long induction workshop for the county executives and chiefs of staff. Wangamati said residents had a lot of hope in the team. "That is why we must let dignity and integrity to be the hallmarks of our conduct at all times," the governor said. He also warned against complacency in the job. Wangamati told told the executives that they had no choice but to deliver promises made to residents. 